Anna Nelson discussed the JFK Assassination Review final report. She was a member of the JFK Records Review Board authorized by the JFK Records Review Act of 1992. She explained that the Oliver Stone movie about the President Kennedy assassination investigation proved to many Americans that there had been a conspiracy and a coverup. Therefore, Congress passed the legislation in 1992, and the Board sought to open every possible record pertaining to the Warren Commission investigation. Professor Nelson also responded to audience telephone calls, faxes, and electronic mail.